article.headline: Chattanooga 74, Murray St. 50
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Kevin Goffney scored 16 points Saturday night to help Chattanooga beat Murray State 74-50 in the Dr. Pepper Tournament. Murray State (5-5) led 2-0 for a few seconds, but quickly saw its lead disappear for good when Marcus Watson hit a 3-pointer to put Chattanooga (8-4) on top. The biggest lead for the Mocs was the final margin. Chattanooga shot 50 percent from the field, compared to 30 percent for Murray State. Marvin Williams led the Racers with 12 points.
